% Goal
Write the `pdd/agentic_common.py` module.

% Role & Scope
Shared infrastructure for agentic CLI invocations (Claude Code, Gemini, Codex, OpenCode). Provides reusable utilities for agent discovery, environment sanitization, logging, model selection, result normalization, and subprocess orchestration. Acts as the low-level interface between PDD orchestrators and external agentic CLIs.

% External Documentation
<claude_code_json_output>
<web>https://claudelog.com/faqs/what-is-output-format-in-claude-code/</web>
</claude_code_json_output>

<gemini_cli_headless>
<web>https://geminicli.com/docs/cli/headless/</web>
</gemini_cli_headless>

<codex_cli_reference>
<web>https://developers.openai.com/codex/cli/reference</web>
</codex_cli_reference>

<opencode_cli_reference>
<web>https://opencode.ai/docs/cli/</web>
</opencode_cli_reference>

% Requirements
1. **Provider Preference**: Private `_DEFAULT_PROVIDER_PREFERENCE = ["anthropic", "google", "openai", "opencode"]`. Public `get_agent_provider_preference() -> List[str]` reads `PDD_AGENTIC_PROVIDER` (comma-sep) or default. `PDD_AGENTIC_PROVIDER=opencode` must route agentic work only through OpenCode.
2. **Logging**: `_log_agentic_interaction` writes to `.pdd/agentic-logs/session_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.jsonl`. Always log provider failures (regardless of verbose mode) so batch sync failures are diagnosable. Only gate successful interaction logging behind `verbose=True`. Additionally, when a CLI exits 0 with empty/whitespace-only stdout, emit a diagnostic console line with stderr tail (last 500 chars), prompt size, sorted auth-env-key names (keys containing `TOKEN` or `API_KEY` with a truthy value), and cwd. This surfaces the blank-provider-error failure mode (cloud one-session sync) in batch logs.
3. **CLI Discovery**: Search via `_find_cli_binary`: `.pddrc` override (`agentic.{name}_path`) → `shutil.which` → `_COMMON_CLI_PATHS` (including `~/.npm-global/bin` for Node-installed CLIs, with nvm glob expansion `~/.nvm/versions/node/*/bin/`). Include `opencode` in `CLI_COMMANDS` and common search paths without requiring setup-detection changes.
4. **Availability**: Anthropic (CLI exists); Google (CLI + `GOOGLE_API_KEY`/`GEMINI_API_KEY`/Vertex or stored Gemini CLI OAuth credentials in `~/.gemini/oauth_creds.json`); OpenAI/Codex (CLI + `OPENAI_API_KEY` or `PDD_CODEX_AUTH_AVAILABLE`); OpenCode (CLI exists, because OpenCode manages provider auth via its own credentials file or provider env vars). The availability check is static and must not imply the Codex ChatGPT token can refresh successfully at execution time. Gemini CLI OAuth is a supported headless path; do not require Google API-key or Vertex env when the CLI has a stored OAuth token.
5. **Execution**: Run in headless mode with JSON output. Sanitize env (TERM=dumb, NO_COLOR=1, CI=1). Strip `PDD_OUTPUT_COST_PATH`. Use `start_new_session=True` via `Popen` to kill process groups on timeout (Issue #830). OpenCode runs non-interactively with `opencode run --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --model <provider/model> <message>` while setting subprocess `cwd` to the worktree; include `--dir <cwd>` only if the installed OpenCode CLI supports it for `run`.
6. **Cost Parsing**:
   - Anthropic: `total_cost_usd` first; fallback to `modelUsage` sum; then token estimation.
   - Google: From `stats["models"]`.
   - OpenAI: From `usage`. Handle NDJSON (`item.completed`, `session.end`, `turn.completed`).
   - OpenCode: Sum numeric `step_finish.part.cost` values from JSON/JSONL events when present; use CSV pricing and token usage only as fallback.
7. **OpenCode Result Normalization**: Accept OpenCode single JSON or JSONL raw events. Normalize `text`, `tool_use`, `step_start`, `step_finish`, and `error` events into PDD's existing `(success, output, cost)` shape. Accumulate text content in event order; include concise tool/step status lines when no assistant text is present; an `error` event returns `success=False` with the error message and any accumulated cost.
8. **OpenCode Model Selection**: `OPENCODE_MODEL` takes precedence. Otherwise use `pdd.DEFAULT_STRENGTH` (the env-overridable `PDD_STRENGTH_DEFAULT`, default `1.0`) as the deterministic strength source for `llm_model.csv` selection, then convert the first supported candidate to OpenCode `provider/model` form. Split model IDs on the first slash only; preserve additional slashes in the model segment, e.g. `openrouter/openai/gpt-5.3-codex`. Provider/model mapping rules: `github_copilot/...` → `github-copilot/...`; `openrouter/...` → `openrouter/...`; `gemini/<model>` from provider `Google Gemini` → `google/<model>`; `vertex_ai/<model>` from provider `Google Vertex AI` → `google-vertex/<model>`; bare models from `Google Gemini` → `google/<model>`; bare models from `Google Vertex AI` → `google-vertex/<model>`; bare models from `OpenAI`, `Anthropic`, `Github Copilot`, or `OpenRouter` use `openai`, `anthropic`, `github-copilot`, or `openrouter` respectively. Skip CSV candidates whose provider prefix/display name cannot be mapped to an OpenCode provider. If every candidate is unsupported or model selection fails, return a clear provider failure rather than invoking OpenCode without a model.
9. **False Positives**: Treat empty output, (zero cost + short output < `MIN_VALID_OUTPUT_LENGTH`), or (cost > 0 + stripped output starts with `Error:` + newlines < `MAX_ERROR_RESPONSE_NEWLINES` + length < 4000) as failure. The `Error:` check must require the stripped output to *start* with `Error:` (a leading prefix of a genuine terse provider-error response) — never an unanchored substring match, which would demote substantive findings that merely *describe* error-raising code (Issue #1232). The newline-count gate (`MAX_ERROR_RESPONSE_NEWLINES = 3`) preserves the long-single-line error case from #902 while protecting multi-paragraph findings docs that happen to start with `Error:`. **Multi-provider configs** (`len(candidates) > 1`): `break` and fall through to the next provider — don't burn retries on a known-broken provider. **Single-provider configs** (`len(candidates) == 1`, e.g. cloud anthropic-only): no fallback exists, so retry on the same provider with exponential backoff (`retry_delay * 2 ** (attempt - 1) + random.uniform(0, retry_delay)`, capped at `MAX_RETRY_DELAY`) up to `max_retries`, then break. An immediate `break` in single-provider configs yields zero retries on transient empty responses and surfaces as the blank-provider-error one-session-sync failure.
10. **Deadline Awareness**: Read `PDD_JOB_DEADLINE`. Skip attempts if remaining < 60s (after 120s reserve).
11. **GitHub State**: Persistence in issue comments via hidden markers (`<!-- PDD_WORKFLOW_STATE:... -->`). `gh api --paginate`.
12. **State Validation**: `validate_cached_state` scans `step_outputs` for "FAILED:" to correct `last_completed_step`.
13. **PR Comments**: Provide `post_pr_comment(repo_owner, repo_name, pr_number, body, cwd) -> bool` that posts a comment to a PR via `gh pr comment {{pr_number}} --repo {repo_owner}/{repo_name} --body ...`. Handle missing `gh` CLI gracefully (return False). This is used by CI validation to report unresolved failures.
14. **Control Token Detection** (4-tier system for parsing workflow control tokens from LLM output):
   - `class TokenMatch`: Dataclass with `tier: str`, `token: Optional[str]`, `pattern: Optional[str]`, `cost: Optional[float]`. `tier` is one of "exact", "case_insensitive", "semantic", "llm_classification". Truthy via `__bool__ = True`.
   - `SEMANTIC_PATTERNS: Dict[str, List[str]]`: Regex patterns for each control token (ALL_TESTS_PASS, NOT_A_BUG, MAX_CYCLES_REACHED, CONTINUE_CYCLE, etc.). Patterns match paraphrased forms like "all N tests pass", "not a bug", "tests still failing".
   - `_SEMANTIC_TAIL_LINES = 30`: Only scan the last 30 lines for semantic patterns (prevents false positives from step output containing these phrases in quoted context).
   - `detect_control_token(output, token, tail_lines=30) -> Optional[TokenMatch]`: 3-tier detection: (1) exact substring, (2) case-insensitive, (3) semantic regex on tail. Returns `TokenMatch` with tier info or `None`. **Tier-3 line splitting must use `str.splitlines()` (portable line-boundary handling for `\n`, `\r\n`, and lone `\r`) — never `str.split('\n')`, which leaves trailing `\r` on each line and produces an extra empty element on CRLF input, shifting the `[-30:]` tail window by one and either excluding semantic phrases at the boundary (CRLF) or collapsing the whole output into one "line" and bypassing the tail restriction (lone `\r`). See Issue #1087.
   - `classify_step_output(output, expected_tokens, model="gemini/gemini-3-flash") -> Optional[TokenMatch]`: Tier-4 fallback — cheap LLM API call with structured JSON to classify output when tiers 1-3 fail. Only call after `detect_control_token` returns `None`.
15. **Retry with Exponential Backoff and Jitter**: `run_agentic_task` retries failed attempts with exponential backoff: `retry_delay * (2 ** (attempt - 1)) + random.uniform(0, retry_delay)`. This prevents thundering herd when concurrent jobs retry simultaneously. Cap maximum backoff at `MAX_RETRY_DELAY = 120`.
16. **Error Classification**: Classify errors from `_run_with_provider` as permanent or transient before deciding to retry:
   - **Permanent** (skip retries, move to next provider): authentication failure, invalid parameter, model not found, unsupported feature, quota exhaustion (TerminalQuotaError, "quota exhausted", "daily quota"). Match via `_is_permanent_error(error_msg) -> bool`.
   - **Transient** (retry with backoff): rate limit (429), server error (5xx), timeout, network error.
   - This prevents wasting 3 retries on errors that won't resolve (e.g., temperature=1 rejection on Vertex AI).
   - Codex stale ChatGPT login failures are permanent and must be normalized before surfacing to users. If OpenAI/Codex exits nonzero and combined stderr/stdout includes Codex websocket/backend auth text such as `access token could not be refreshed`, `please sign in again`, `chatgpt.com/backend-api/codex`, `codex/responses`, plus `401`/`Unauthorized`/sign-in language, return a concise message telling the user to run `codex login` (or `codex login --device-auth`; `codex login --with-api-key` for API-key auth). Do not expose raw websocket URLs/log noise as the main failure.
17. **Aggregate Per-Step Timeout**: For local runs without `PDD_JOB_DEADLINE`, default to `2 * effective_timeout` as the step deadline. This caps worst-case to 2x the step timeout instead of 9x (3 providers x 3 retries).
18. **Progress Tracking** (Ctrl+C UX):
   - `set_agentic_progress(workflow, current_step, total_steps, step_name, completed_steps)`: Record current progress so KeyboardInterrupt can report how far the workflow got.
   - `clear_agentic_progress()`: Clear progress state.
   - `get_and_clear_agentic_interrupt_context() -> Optional[Dict]`: Retrieve and clear progress for Ctrl+C reporting.
19. **Template Variable Substitution**: `substitute_template_variables(template, context, *, strict_unresolved=False) -> str`: Safe substitution that handles curly braces in LLM output without raising KeyError, with optional strict unresolved-placeholder checking.
20. **Post Final Comment**: `post_final_comment(repo_owner, repo_name, issue_number, reason, total_cost, steps_completed, total_steps, cwd) -> bool`: Post workflow summary comment to GitHub issue when a workflow stops early.

% Function Signatures
`get_agent_provider_preference() -> List[str]`
`get_available_agents() -> List[str]`
`run_agentic_task(instruction, cwd, *, verbose=False, quiet=False, label="", timeout=None, max_retries=1, retry_delay=DEFAULT_RETRY_DELAY, deadline=None, use_playwright=False, reasoning_time: Optional[float] = None) -> Tuple[bool, str, float, str]`
- Tries providers in preference order. Returns (success, output, cost, provider).
- `use_playwright` enables constrained tools (see section).
- Uses exponential backoff with jitter: `retry_delay * (2 ** (attempt - 1)) + random.uniform(0, retry_delay)`.
- Classifies errors as permanent/transient via `_is_permanent_error()` before retrying.
- Enforces aggregate per-step timeout (`2 * effective_timeout` when no deadline set).
`detect_control_token(output, token, tail_lines=_SEMANTIC_TAIL_LINES) -> Optional[TokenMatch]`
`classify_step_output(output, expected_tokens, model="gemini/gemini-3-flash") -> Optional[TokenMatch]`
`_codex_auth_failure_message(error_detail: str) -> Optional[str]`
`substitute_template_variables(template, context, *, strict_unresolved=False) -> str`
`set_agentic_progress(workflow, current_step, total_steps, step_name, completed_steps) -> None`
`clear_agentic_progress() -> None`
`get_and_clear_agentic_interrupt_context() -> Optional[Dict]`
`get_job_deadline() -> Optional[float]`
`post_step_comment(repo_owner, repo_name, issue_number, step_num, total_steps, description, output, cwd) -> bool`
`post_pr_comment(repo_owner, repo_name, pr_number, body, cwd) -> bool`
`post_final_comment(repo_owner, repo_name, issue_number, reason, total_cost, steps_completed, total_steps, cwd) -> bool`
`validate_cached_state(last_completed_step, step_outputs, step_order=None, quiet=False) -> Union[int, float]`
`load_workflow_state(...) -> Tuple[Optional[Dict], Optional[int]]`
`save_workflow_state(...) -> Optional[int]` - Must return `None` on GitHub failure (Issue #830).
`clear_workflow_state(...) -> None`

% Constants
- `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS: 600.0`
- `MIN_VALID_OUTPUT_LENGTH: 50`
- `DEFAULT_MAX_RETRIES: 3`
- `JOB_TIMEOUT_MARGIN_SECONDS: 120.0`
- `MIN_ATTEMPT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS: 60.0`
- `MAX_ERROR_SNIPPET_LENGTH: 2000`
- `MAX_ERROR_RESPONSE_NEWLINES: 3` (Issue #1232: newline-count gate for leading-`Error:` false-positive heuristic)

% Token Pricing
`Pricing(input_per_million, output_per_million, cached_input_multiplier)`
- `GEMINI`: flash (0.35/1.05, 0.5), pro (3.50/10.50, 0.5)
- `CODEX`: 1.50/6.00, 0.25
- `ANTHROPIC`: opus (15/75, 0.1), sonnet (3/15, 0.1), haiku (0.8/4, 0.1).
- Formula: `new_input = max(0, total_input - cached)`. Anthropic: `new_input = total - cache_read - cache_write`. Cache write billed at 1.25x input.

% CLI Discovery
`_find_cli_binary(name, config=None) -> Optional[str]`
`_load_agentic_config() -> Dict`
`_get_cli_diagnostic_info(name) -> str`

% CLI Invocation
Instruction: `"Read the file {prompt_file} for instructions. You have full file access to explore and modify files as needed."`
- Anthropic: `[cli_path, "-p", "-", "--dangerously-skip-permissions", "--output-format", "json"]` (pipe via stdin).
- Google: `[cli_path, "<instruction>", "--yolo", "--output-format", "json"]`.
- OpenAI: `[cli_path, "exec", "--sandbox", <mode>, "--json", <path>]`. Mode default: `danger-full-access`.
- OpenCode: `[cli_path, "run", "--format", "json", "--dangerously-skip-permissions", "--model", <mapped_provider_model>, "Read the file <prompt_file_name> for your full instructions and execute them."]`, with subprocess `cwd` set to the target worktree. If the installed `opencode run` supports `--dir`, include `--dir`, `str(cwd)`.

% Playwright Mode (`use_playwright=True`)
- Anthropic: Replaces `--dangerously-skip-permissions` with `--allowedTools`, `"Bash"`, `"Read"`, `"Write"`, `--max-turns`, `"30"`.
- Google/OpenAI/OpenCode: Same as standard (no per-tool restrictions).

% GitHub State Persistence
- `_find_state_comment`: Use `gh api ... --paginate`.
- `save_workflow_state`: Local first, then GitHub. If `github_save_state` returns `None`, return `None` (detect divergence).

% Instructions
1. Implement `_subprocess_run` using `Popen(..., start_new_session=True)`. Catch `TimeoutExpired` and kill process group (`-proc.pid`).
2. `run_agentic_task`: Inject `PDD_USER_FEEDBACK` if present. Use exponential backoff with jitter for retries: `backoff = retry_delay * (2 ** (attempt - 1)) + random.uniform(0, retry_delay)`, capped at `MAX_RETRY_DELAY`. Classify errors via `_is_permanent_error()` before retrying — permanent errors skip retries and move to next provider. For OpenAI/Codex nonzero exits, `_run_with_provider` must inspect combined stderr/stdout with `_codex_auth_failure_message()` before returning a generic `Exit code ...` string, so stale Codex login failures become actionable `codex login` guidance and remain permanent.
3. Detect single-letter files `C`, `E`, `T` after success; log red warning via `console.print`.
4. `_parse_provider_json`:
   - Anthropic: `result` or `response`. If `data.get("is_error")` is truthy (Claude Code session failed — auth error, refusal, crash, e.g. `{"is_error": true, "result": "Not logged in - Please run /login"}`), return `(False, text, cost)` so the caller treats it as a real failure instead of empty success.
   - Google: `result`, `response`, or `output`.
   - OpenAI (0.104.0+): `data["item"]["text"]` if `item["type"] == "agent_message"`, else fallback.
   - OpenCode: handle parsed event aggregates or a single raw event object; return failure for `error`, otherwise return accumulated text/status and authoritative summed `step_finish.part.cost`.
5. Support model overrides: `CLAUDE_MODEL`, `GEMINI_MODEL`, `CODEX_MODEL`, `OPENCODE_MODEL`.
6. Reasoning effort: `_run_with_provider` resolves a generic `reasoning_effort` from (a) explicit `reasoning_time` kwarg only when the caller forwarded a user-supplied `--time` (commands gate on `ctx.obj["time_explicit"]` — never pass the `DEFAULT_TIME` fallback) or (b) `PDD_REASONING_EFFORT` env var (validated against `{low, medium, high}`; any other value is ignored to prevent argv poisoning). For Codex, additionally check `CODEX_REASONING_EFFORT` env var first — it accepts `{low, medium, high, xhigh}` (xhigh is Codex-only, used by the cloud worker for GPT-5.4 routing) and takes precedence over the generic `reasoning_effort`. Inject `-c model_reasoning_effort=<level>` **before** the `exec` subcommand — Codex treats `-c` / `--config` as top-level flags only and silently ignores them after `exec`. Anthropic and Gemini CLIs have no reasoning-effort flag today; emit a one-line notice in non-quiet mode rather than silently dropping the signal.

